headline.main: DESERT ARMIES CUT; Germans and Italians Hemmed In East of Tobruk Are Pounded NEW DRIVE STARTED WEST R.A.F. Continues to Blast at Axis Columns -- Annihilation of Division Staff Claimed BRITISH TRAP UNITS OF FOES IN LIBYA

lead_paragraph: CAIRO, Egypt, Nov. 28 -- British Imperials widened their wedge through the main Axis battle line below Tobruk tonight and one British force pressed on west through Libya, paced by the Royal Air Force, which reported it had blown up with a well-placed load of bombs the whole field headquarters staff of one Italian division.
